==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[μύθος]] (''mythos''), report, tale, story.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|mythoi}} 

# A [[story]] or set of stories [[relevant]] or having a significant [[truth]] or [[meaning]] to a particular [[culture]], [[religion]], [[society]], [[group]], etc. 
# Anything delivered by [[word of mouth]], [[word]], [[speech]], [[conversation]]; a [[story]], [[tale]] or [[legend]], especially the [[poetic]] tale.    
# A tale, story or [[narrative]], usually verbally transmitted, or recorded into the written from an alleged secondary source.

